This project is inspired by STORM (Synthesis of Topic Outlines through
Retrieval and Multi-perspective Question Asking), developed by the Stanford
Open Virtual Assistant Lab (OVAL) and released under the MIT License:

    https://github.com/stanford-oval/storm

This repository re-implements the STORM *method* (multi-perspective,
retrieval-grounded question asking → outline → grounded draft → review) as a
native Claude skill. It does not include or redistribute any source code from
the original STORM project.

References:
- STORM    — Shao et al., NAACL 2024 — https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.14207
- Co-STORM — Jiang et al., EMNLP 2024 — https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.15232

STORM and Co-STORM are the work of their respective authors. This project is
not affiliated with or endorsed by Stanford OVAL.
